[DhtmlXQ_comment0]sg 20120924 1985 ncsc Liu Dianzhong W Chen Xiaokun C16||ECCO: C16 Central cannon with riverbank cannon vs Screen Horse Defense.||ECCO:C16 ????????? ||||Tis game was played in round 7 of the 1985 Chinese National Singles Championships. The attacking moves in the final stage were quite exciting, and had an element of composed endgames. ||Jim:Very exciting game![/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment9]And the basic opening was now determined.||Red has used the Central Cannon with riverbank chariot variation while black has chosen the Screen Horse Defense with 3rd Pawn Advancement Variation.||Red's riverbank chariot allows red to have a more steadfast game.||C8=7, P3+1 and R9+1 are other viable options for red.||  ||||Jim: The name of the opening by the GM is named so. It is quite different from the ECCO system that came later.[/DhtmlXQ_comment9]
[DhtmlXQ_comment10]With this move, black aims to prevent red from playing P7+1.||Another option would be to play P7+1 now.[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
[DhtmlXQ_comment16]Black plays the side cannnon so that he has the option of playing R1+4.[/DhtmlXQ_comment16]
[DhtmlXQ_comment22]This move was controversial. In retrospect, it might be the cause of black's demise.||Perhaps C1+4 followed by R1+3 would have been a better option.[/DhtmlXQ_comment22]
