[DhtmlXQ_comment33]A must make move! Blacks central cannon may look menacing but black does not have any other supporting material to help out.||Red has the material advantage and has the game under control.?[/DhtmlXQ_comment33]
[DhtmlXQ_comment34]Black is forced to make this move.||If the red horse was not captured, red would play H7-9 for the kill.[/DhtmlXQ_comment34]
[DhtmlXQ_comment43]By retreating the horse, red now has a checkmate option of C9+3.||A better move would have been to play C9=3 to pin the black horse. Red would have control of the game firmly in hand. Unfortunately, I was not able to have detected that move as I was carried away with my original game plan.||This is a mistake that all players should be wary off. Never be too engrossed with your original game plan that you fail to notice other opportunities that present themselves.||One must always play the game according to the circumstances that present themselves and never be  carried away by irrational results. This is one of the fatal flaws in actual play.[/DhtmlXQ_comment43]
